reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought a new dishwasher that was a little loud and made the countertop hot above it. Put two layers of this around the top and sides of it and it significantly improved. Not like it was silent but a lot better. Inexpensive upgrade.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to work with, helps to block air movement
reviews.reviewText: It seems to have worked for my purpose. The exterior wall behind my dishwasher was drafty and the water line would freeze when the temperature got into the single digits. This helps to cut the draft, and along with insulating the water line, it should improve my situation.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not for intended use
reviews.reviewText: Bought to stuff between the exterior wall and lath in a 1900 year old house. Following installation of new pocket replacement windows.There’s several cavities beneath the kitchen window. Foamed around and the sill. But don’t wanna mess with the pee trap for the sink inside the wall or wire to the new outlet.We’re using this to stuff inside the crevices since pink insulation tends to collapse over time. This won’t. It’ll be dense enough tucked to add a barrier.We’ve used denim like wool insulation in other rooms along the cracks behind the trim while restore trim. This product is similar. Though much thinner.Since we’re tucking it in the spaces should work well long term.Based on description expected twice as thick. Why only four stars. For a dishwasher should be adequate.
